    .preface
      .row.centered
        section.col-6
          p.tagline A thin namespaced localStorage API.
          p.blurb.
            tote is a tiny JavaScript library that turns localStorage into isolated containers. 
            You can store multiple sets of data in the same app without fear of key collisions.
          p As a bonus, you get to store and retrive Integer, Strings, Booleans, whatever -- not just strings!

        section.synopsis.col-6
          :markdown
            ```javascript
            var about = tote('about-tote');

            about.set('tags', ['simple', 'tiny']);
            console.log( about.get('tags') );
            // ['simple', 'tiny']

            about.set('isActive', true);
            console.log( about.get('isActive') );
            // true
            ```

